{"overview":"This E-minor piece is a compact ternary nocturne whose most distinctive feature is its restless network of secondary diminished seventh chords and secondary dominants, weaving chromatic intensification through an otherwise diatonic framework as the lyrical A theme undergoes successive ornamentation and elaboration across three returns. The middle section's diatonic pivot to B major and C# minor provides a momentary luminous contrast before the richly embellished recapitulation drives toward a quiet, ethereal coda that resolves the tonal tension with sustained arpeggiated sonorities.","cross_piece_tags":["nocturne","ternary","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","melancholic","meditative","circle_of_fifths","modal_mixture"]}
